{
  "stem": "150.1",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They sorted them out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They took away the old and the-- and the sick and the young, and they let the other people come back.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as we were-- we still didn't know what was going on.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "As the people were coming in, all of a sudden the door flies open.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And a German officer comes running in, who apparently was just checking out to see, you know-- I don't know what he was checking out.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But he found us, not knowing that we were not among those who had never been taken away.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he started asking questions of the adults, and the adults did not really know what to answer.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They didn't want to be caught.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But it all went off well.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We had no idea whether my mother was still alive, and naturally, we rushed back.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And apparently, it was only that particular section of the ghetto that was affected.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And my mother was going out of her mind, knowing that we had gone to where this thing was taking place.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Eventually, eventually.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But while in the ghetto-- well, the big Aktion took place on October 29, 1942.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was at a time when we had about 32,000 people left in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We started with around 48,000.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were told that everybody had to report to this large field in the center of the ghetto, and anybody found in the houses would be immediately executed.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So all of us showed up, and there was a bunch of Germans sitting at a long table on one side of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we marched past, and there was one German who would go right, left, left, right, sorting us all out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And all the people to the right were taken to one side.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
